{
  "skyrimnet_knowledge_pack": {
    "author": "WinterishClover",
    "description": "World knowledge for Become High King of Skyrim: The Next Generation v2.0. Covers Highreach Keep history and lore, ruler identity and gender, royal marriage and divorce, kingdom governance systems, per-hold approval, faith, economy, taxation, rebellion, Church of Skyrim declarations, royal decrees, desperate measures, trade policy, and loan status. Entries are regionally gated by hold faction membership and scaled by importance. All rulership entries require AAIsHighKing to be active.",
    "entries": [
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "",
        "content": "Highreach Keep is a city hidden within the Jerall Mountains, south of Falkreath Hold. Long dismissed as legend, it re-emerged publicly in 4E 175. It is accessible through passes in the mountains and contains a city, castle and ancient history.",
        "display_name": "Highreach Keep - Existence and Location",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Jerall Mountains",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "location",
          "jerall",
          "city"
        ],
        "type": "LOCATION"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "",
        "content": "Highreach Keep is a large, diverse city with a gladiatorial arena, guild hall, shops, barracks, a hall of the dead, a prison, Coldrun Lake, and Highreach Castle - the seat of royal power. It is self-sustaining and has been so for centuries.",
        "display_name": "Highreach Keep - City Features",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "location",
          "city",
          "arena",
          "castle"
        ],
        "type": "LOCATION"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "The valley containing Highreach was created in 1E 2703 when a catastrophic landslide at Pale Pass buried the Akaviri invaders. The violence tore a hidden cleft from the Jerall Mountains. Later generations believed it was the hand of Shor and Kyne - a divine blow to preserve the North.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - Valley Origin",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.6,
        "location": "Jerall Mountains",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "founding",
          "history",
          "akaviri",
          "jerall"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "Highreach was founded around 2E 577 by the Silent Accord, a secret alliance of nobles from Falkreath, the Pale, and Bruma. Bound by blood, trade, and fear of political ruin, they chose to build a sanctuary in the hidden valley - not to conquer, but to endure.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Silent Accord Founding",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "founding",
          "silent accord",
          "second era",
          "history"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "The Rootbind Covenant were Argonian scholars and survivors of the Knahaten Flu who helped build Highreach. They brought forgotten knowledge: how to draw warmth from the earth, bind stone without fault, and fold memory into walls. Without them, the Keep would never have stood.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Rootbind Covenant",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.65,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "rootbind",
          "argonian",
          "founding",
          "dwemer"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "The descendants of the Rootbind Covenant, called Root-Wardens, still live in Highreach. They maintain the geothermal systems that keep the valley warm, continuing a tradition of quiet, essential service that dates back to the city's founding.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - Root-Warden Descendants",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.5,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "rootbind",
          "root-warden",
          "argonian",
          "geothermal"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "Highreach's first king was a nameless Breton wanderer who rose not by bloodline, but by deed. He led his people through famine and peril, earning the crown by merit alone. When reckless hands damaged the Dwemer systems beneath the Keep, he descended alone to fix them and never returned. His sacrifice is remembered as the bedrock of Highreach's spirit.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Nameless King",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.75,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "nameless king",
          "breton",
          "founding",
          "history",
          "sacrifice"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAKingHighreachCitizens\")",
        "content": "Despite sitting high in the Jerall Mountains, Highreach enjoys a temperate climate. Geothermal rivers beneath the city emit constant warmth, and the mountain walls block northern winds while funneling warmer western breezes through the valley. Birch and maple grow where only pine should survive.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - Climate Paradox",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.6,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "climate",
          "geothermal",
          "agriculture",
          "jerall"
        ],
        "type": "LOCATION"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "In 3E 432, fearing Thalmor agents, Highreach's Shadow Council voted to collapse the mountain passes and seal the city away. The following year, an Oblivion Gate erupted from Coldrun Lake inside the sealed valley. The city was trapped, unable to flee or receive aid. Four hundred seventeen citizens died defending Highreach before the gate was closed. The city remained sealed for 150 years afterward, a period known as the Long Silence.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Long Silence and Sealing",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.65,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "oblivion crisis",
          "long silence",
          "history",
          "tragedy",
          "shadow council"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "In 4E 175, following the White-Gold Concordat and the Thalmor threat, Highreach opened its gates and formally announced itself to Skyrim after 150 years of isolation. The city offered itself as the ancient seat of High Kings. High King Torygg visited in 4E 176 and was impressed, but declined to relocate the capital.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Emergence (4E 175)",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "emergence",
          "fourth era",
          "torygg",
          "history"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "Since re-emerging, Highreach occupies a strange political place in Skyrim. It has trade agreements and limited Moot participation, but holds no real governance role. The holds acknowledge it, trade with it, but do not consult it. Its historical claim as the seat of High Kings is treated as interesting trivia rather than precedent.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - Political Marginalization",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.55,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "politics",
          "skyrim",
          "moot",
          "history"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAKingHighreachCitizens\")",
        "content": "The Celestium is a towering crystalline spire at the heart of Highreach's town square. It casts a pillar of light visible from every tier of the city and hums faintly at sunrise. Most think it ceremonial, but scholars believe it is a Dwemer energy dispersal column integrated by the Rootbind Covenant to stabilize the volcanic systems beneath the Keep.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Celestium",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.5,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "celestium",
          "dwemer",
          "landmark",
          "rootbind"
        ],
        "type": "LOCATION"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAKingHighreachCitizens\")",
        "content": "Above Highreach Castle, carved into the mountainside, stands the Summit of Two Wills - a monument depicting Queen Vaelora and her cousin Cairn Halwerd at the moment she halted his campaign of expansion with a single line: 'We were not made to conquer - we were made to last.' It is Highreach's defining symbol of restraint over ambition.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - The Summit of Two Wills",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.5,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "monument",
          "vaelora",
          "history",
          "landmark"
        ],
        "type": "LOCATION"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAKingHighreachCitizens\")",
        "content": "Highreach has a working gladiatorial arena. Criminals condemned by the crown may be sentenced to fight for their freedom rather than face execution, providing both justice and spectacle for citizens.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - Gladiatorial Arena",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.45,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "arena",
          "gladiator",
          "justice",
          "entertainment"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "",
        "content": "Highreach Keep claims to be the ancient seat of High Kings of Skyrim - a title older than Solitude's political dominance. This claim was formally made when the city re-emerged in 4E 175, but went largely unrecognized until recently.",
        "display_name": "Highreach - Historical Seat of High Kings",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.65,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "highreach",
          "high king",
          "skyrim",
          "legitimacy",
          "history"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": true,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingPlayerGender\") == 0",
        "content": "{{player name}} is the High King of Skyrim, ruling from Highreach Keep. He earned the crown through the ancient Moot of Jarls. All NPCs should address him with masculine royal titles such as 'my King', 'Your Grace', 'my liege', or 'the High King'. He governs with a council of advisors and manages the welfare of all nine holds.",
        "display_name": "Ruler Identity - High King",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.95,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "high king",
          "player",
          "identity",
          "ruling",
          "highreach",
          "gender"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": true,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingPlayerGender\") == 1",
        "content": "{{player name}} is the High Queen of Skyrim, ruling from Highreach Keep. She earned the crown through the ancient Moot of Jarls. All NPCs should address her with feminine royal titles such as 'my Queen', 'Your Grace', 'my liege', or 'the High Queen'. She governs with a council of advisors and manages the welfare of all nine holds.",
        "display_name": "Ruler Identity - High Queen",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.95,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "high queen",
          "player",
          "identity",
          "ruling",
          "highreach",
          "gender"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": true,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingPlayerGender\") == 2",
        "content": "{{player name}} is the High Monarch of Skyrim, ruling from Highreach Keep. They earned the crown through the ancient Moot of Jarls. All NPCs should address them with gender-neutral royal titles such as 'my Monarch', 'Your Grace', 'my liege', or 'the High Monarch'. They govern with a council of advisors and manage the welfare of all nine holds.",
        "display_name": "Ruler Identity - High Monarch",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.95,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "high monarch",
          "player",
          "identity",
          "ruling",
          "highreach",
          "gender"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingHasRoyalSpouse\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAMarriageSpouseChoice\") == 1",
        "content": "{{player name}} has taken Elisif the Fair as Royal Spouse. The former Jarl of Solitude now sits beside the throne at Highreach Keep. Their union is a political alliance as much as a personal bond, merging the old ruling line of Haafingar with the new crown. Citizens across Skyrim know of the royal marriage.",
        "display_name": "Royal Marriage - Elisif the Fair",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.6,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "marriage",
          "elisif",
          "royal spouse",
          "haafingar",
          "highreach"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingHasRoyalSpouse\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAMarriageSpouseChoice\") == 2",
        "content": "{{player name}} has taken Ulfric Stormcloak as Royal Spouse. The former Jarl of Windhelm now sits beside the throne at Highreach Keep. Their union is a political alliance as much as a personal bond, merging the Stormcloak legacy with the new crown. Citizens across Skyrim know of the royal marriage.",
        "display_name": "Royal Marriage - Ulfric Stormcloak",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.6,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "marriage",
          "ulfric",
          "royal spouse",
          "windhelm",
          "highreach"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingDivorced\") == 1",
        "content": "{{player name}} has divorced their Royal Spouse. The marriage that once united the crown with a powerful house has been dissolved by royal decree. The divorce cost the treasury dearly and shook the faith of the people. It remains a topic of gossip and disapproval across Skyrim.",
        "display_name": "Royal Divorce",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.65,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "divorce",
          "royal spouse",
          "scandal",
          "faith",
          "gossip"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingDivorceExile\") == 1",
        "content": "{{player name}} not only divorced their Royal Spouse but had them exiled from Skyrim entirely. The former spouse has vanished and is no longer seen anywhere in the realm. This ruthless act has become infamous - whispered about in taverns and condemned by priests. Many see it as proof of the ruler's capacity for cruelty.",
        "display_name": "Royal Divorce - Spouse Exiled",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "divorce",
          "exile",
          "royal spouse",
          "cruelty",
          "scandal"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAAbdicated\") == 1",
        "content": "{{player name}} has abdicated the throne of Skyrim. The crown that was won through the Moot of Jarls has been voluntarily surrendered. Skyrim is without a High King once more. The realm buzzes with uncertainty - some mourn the loss of leadership, others see opportunity in the power vacuum.",
        "display_name": "Abdication of the Throne",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.9,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "abdication",
          "throne",
          "high king",
          "moot",
          "power vacuum"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingFaction\")",
        "content": "The ruler of Skyrim governs with a council of twelve advisors: the Grand Advisor, High Priest, Master of Coin, Lord Commander, First Mage, Will of the Crown, Voice of the Crown, Master of Assassins, Royal Chronicler, Royal Steward, Royal Blacksmith, and Royal Spouse. Each holds real power and responsibility within the kingdom.",
        "display_name": "The Royal Council of Twelve",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "council",
          "advisors",
          "highreach",
          "government"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingCouncilFaction\")",
        "content": "The crown funds weekly expenses across several categories: guards who patrol the holds, street lighting for safety, water systems for public health, infrastructure maintenance for roads and buildings, castle upkeep, and appointed priest salaries where the Church of Skyrim has been declared. These expenses are managed by the Will of the Crown and paid from the royal treasury.",
        "display_name": "Kingdom Expenses and Infrastructure",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.5,
        "location": "Skyrim",
        "tags": [
          "expenses",
          "guards",
          "infrastructure",
          "treasury",
          "government"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_quest_stage(\"AAStrmCrownQuest\") >= 10 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"AAHighKingCouncilFaction\")",
        "content": "The Stormcrown is a legendary artifact connected to the Highreach throne. It carries both a curse and a blessing that intensifies based on how the ruler governs - righteousness strengthens its power, while tyranny deepens its curse.",
        "display_name": "The Stormcrown",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.6,
        "location": "Highreach Keep",
        "tags": [
          "stormcrown",
          "artifact",
          "high king",
          "highreach",
          "curse",
          "blessing"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAApprovalTierWhiterun\") == 0 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"CrimeFactionWhiterun\")",
        "content": "The people of Whiterun Hold despise the crown. Approval of {{player name}}'s rule is dangerously low. Citizens are angry, fearful, and speak openly of revolt. Guards are tense. Merchants worry about unrest. The ruler's name is spoken with contempt in the streets of Whiterun.",
        "display_name": "Approval Despised - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "approval",
          "despised",
          "unrest",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAApprovalTierWhiterun\") == 4 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"CrimeFactionWhiterun\")",
        "content": "The people of Whiterun Hold adore the crown. Approval of {{player name}}'s rule is absolute. Citizens speak the ruler's name with pride and genuine loyalty. Guards stand tall and are honored to serve. Merchants thrive under the crown's favor. Whiterun celebrates its ruler.",
        "display_name": "Approval Beloved - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.7,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "approval",
          "beloved",
          "loyalty",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingCourtHasPriest\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAFaithTierWhiterun\") == 0 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"JobPriestFaction\")",
        "content": "Faith in the crown's religious authority is nonexistent in Whiterun Hold. The people see {{player name}} as a heretic or false prophet. Priests and devout citizens speak openly against the throne's spiritual claims. The crown's religious decrees carry no weight here.",
        "display_name": "Faith Collapsed - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.9,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "faith",
          "heretic",
          "religion",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingCourtHasPriest\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAFaithTierWhiterun\") == 4 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"JobPriestFaction\")",
        "content": "Faith in the crown's religious authority is absolute in Whiterun Hold. The people regard {{player name}} as divinely chosen. Priests speak of the ruler with reverence, and the faithful consider it an honor to serve the throne. Religious devotion to the crown runs deep in Whiterun.",
        "display_name": "Faith Absolute - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.9,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "faith",
          "saint",
          "devotion",
          "religion",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKingHoldWhiterunChurchDeclared\") == 1 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"CrimeFactionWhiterun\")",
        "content": "The Church of Skyrim has been officially established in Whiterun Hold. The old Divines' altars and shrines have been replaced with monuments to the crown. An appointed priest serves the ruler's spiritual authority in Whiterun. This is a permanent change that has reshaped religious life in the hold - some embrace it, others quietly resent the loss of the old ways.",
        "display_name": "Church of Skyrim Declared - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.75,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "church",
          "religion",
          "declared",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKing_EconomyScore_Whiterun\") <= 30 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"JobMerchantFaction\") and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"CrimeFactionWhiterun\")",
        "content": "The economy in Whiterun Hold is in severe decline. Merchants can barely keep their doors open, trade routes are drying up, and coin is scarce. Shopkeepers in Whiterun speak of hardship and ruin. Empty market stalls and closed shops are becoming common.",
        "display_name": "Economy Collapsing - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.75,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "economy",
          "collapse",
          "trade",
          "merchant",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AAKing_EconomyScore_Whiterun\") >= 70 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"JobMerchantFaction\") and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"CrimeFactionWhiterun\")",
        "content": "The economy in Whiterun Hold is thriving. Merchants are prosperous, trade flows freely, and coin is plentiful. Shopkeepers in Whiterun praise the crown's economic stewardship. Markets are bustling and new trade opportunities abound.",
        "display_name": "Economy Thriving - Whiterun",
        "emotion": "",
        "importance": 0.75,
        "location": "Whiterun Hold",
        "tags": [
          "economy",
          "thriving",
          "trade",
          "prosperity",
          "whiterun",
          "whiterun"
        ],
        "type": "KNOWLEDGE"
      },
      {
        "always_inject": false,
        "condition_expr": "get_global_value(\"AAIsHighKing\") == 1 and get_global_value(\"AATax_Rate_Whiterun\") <= 5 and is_in_faction(actorUUID, \"CrimeFactionWhiterun\")",
        "content": "Tax rates in Whiterun Hold are very low. Citizens appreciate the crown's light hand on their purses. Merchants and common folk alike speak well of the tax policy. People in Whiterun feel they can breathe freely and keep more of what they earn.",
